The 23rd Edition being held from 15th – 17th February, 2023 at Biswa Bangla Mela Prangan, Kolkata, West Bengal, India –promises to be even bigger and better in terms of size and participation. IISS 2023 will showcase Domestic and Overseas Participants, in terms of Stalls, Delegates and Trade Visitors in a scenic and natural ambience.\n
The Show will highlight India’s commitment towards safe and sustainable seafood production for export.\n
Meet face to face with seafood buyers across the world, discover new business relationships, and increase your sales/exports at one of Asia’s largest Seafood Exposition. Participate and Meet with top Seafood Buyers from Retail and Food Service Industries, Network with Wholesalers, Distributors, Importers and Exporters making business in India, a truly global experience.

1. 23rd India International Seafood Show 2023 will be organized in Biswa Bangla Mela Prangan, Kolkata,\n India from 15th - 17th February 2023.
2. The Exhibitors shall adhere to the exhibition manual (Available on Website: www.indianseafoodexpo.com).
3. Exhibitor may book any number of stalls. Stalls will be allotted on a first-come-first served basis.

4. GST applicable will be additional to the fees mentioned. For the stall registration within Kolkata, the GST should be in SGST (9%) & CGST (9%), whereas for the stalls outside Kolkata, it should be IGST (18%).
5. Fee once paid will not be refunded.
6. The Organizers will provide standard fascia with company name for shell scheme.
7. 2 free exhibitor passes will be provided per 9 sq m stall booked.
8. For each 3X3 m shell scheme stall, one counter table, one round table, 3 chairs, one power outlet, (5A, 230 V), three spot lights and one waste basket.
9. 25 free passes for one time entry will be provided to each exhibitor.
10. Exhibitors opting for raw space need to inform the Organizers by 10th January 2023 along with a layout plan for approval.
11. Exhibitor can order additional furniture/other items/ additional electricity requirements directly with the official stall contractor. Extra charges apply for additional requirements.
12. For raw space the stall will behanded over to the Exhibitors on 12/02/2023 at 10.00am and for shell scheme the stall will behanded over to Exhibitor on 14/02/2023 by 10:00 am.
13. Heavy machinery for display needs to be placed inside before 12 PM on 11/02/2023.
14. Furnishing of stall shall be completed and all materials that are not for use should be removed by 18.00 hrs on 14/02/2023.
15. The name of the Exhibit or registered on or before 20th January 2023 only will be published in the show catalogue.
17. Stall Delegates are entitled to participate in the technical sessions arranged by the Organizers.
18. Exhibitors should participate in the show without causing any disturbance to neighboring stalls.
19. Any cultural performance within the booth is to be limited within the scope of the show, that too with the prior permission from the organizer.
20. Confirmation of Stall reservations will be sent by E-mail.
21. Though the fair authorities will be providing general security, the fair authorities will not be responsible for any damage/loss of any article/property kept in the stall.
22. All products shall be exhibited only with in the stall.

23. The Organizers reserve the right to make such changes in stall position, site layout, floor plan and other details as they consider fit in the overall interest and safety precautions of the exhibition and adhering to the norms of the Local Governing body.

24. The Exhibitor shall be liable to pay for any damages caused to the stall or equipment allotted to him. Any such damages shall be assessed by the Organizers and their decision on the charges to be paid by the Exhibitor shall be final.
25. Jurisdiction in any case of dispute will be Ernakulam, Kerala, India.
